txt.en: 'Several of the carriers I sent to Arhaim have not returned. I suspect the 'Orc activity' these Beornings mentioned was their attacks on my men! The Beornings will not allow me to cross and reclaim my stolen goods. If you are heading in there to deal with the Orcs, will you please keep an eye out for any of my supplies?'
Orcs have attacked many traders on the road in Duskenvale and stolen their supplies. The trader Lúfred has asked you to retrieve the wares.
'Thank you, [placeholder]. At least I am able to recoup some of my losses. A shame that lives were lost to those brutes.'
Orcs have stolen many traders' wares by ambushing them on the road to Arhaim.\n\nYou should collect the stolen supplies from the Orc camp Brafulug.
You have retrieved the stolen supplies from the Orc camp.\n\nYou should return to Lúfred at the Beorning watchpost to inform him.
